description: 2008-2010 Royal Air Force: C2ISR Tactics and Training Role Officer, Air Warfare Centre • Actively selected, as a result of previous successful tours, to fill this very high profile job. • Solely responsible for the development and publication of the first Joint Intelligence, Surveillance & Reconnaissance Tactics Handbook. • Causing a cultural shift within the RAF hierarchy that allowed for the introduction of holistic Intelligence, Surveillance & Reconnaissance training. • Socialising Intelligence, Surveillance & Reconnaissance training to senior RAF Board members, peers and to the civilian academic community. • Solely responsible for the inception, introduction, development and delivery of the Expert Level, Qualified Weapons Instructor (Intelligence, Surveillance & Reconnaissance) Course. • Selecting and training the first wave of Intelligence, Surveillance & Reconnaissance instructors. • Tasked with transposing technical capability to tactical employment and translating tactical need to technical requirement. • Targeted by senior management to provide advice on Intelligence, Surveillance & Reconnaissance policy and developing future road mapping. • Advising the Air Warfare Centre and MOD senior executives on C4 and Integrated Intelligence Officer training and the Intelligence Competency (training) Framework. • Responsible for providing unimpeachable tactical advise to front line commanders and Squadrons. • Advising the Home Office on the integration of military Intelligence, Surveillance & Reconnaissance capabilities in supporting National operations.

description: Reference: This has been a highly impressive year for Stockbridge with numerous notable achievements. In support of Op HERRICK he has developed several novel TTPs, crafted a comprehensive ISR Tactics Book and completed an ISR Planning Guide. His magnificent efforts highlight his immense knowledge of the entire gamut of ISR capabilities and his deep understanding of the broader operational picture. Demonstrating great vision, drive and leadership he identified the requirement for, and developed and delivered, the ISR(QWI) Cse, including its integration into the CQWI ex. His superb efforts culminated in the graduation of the first QWIs in Jul 10. Throughout this period Stockbridge has demonstrated the level of intelligence, initiative and innovation associated with higher rank. A lateral thinker he has consistently identified opportunities for improvement, and has demonstrated the energy and strength of leadership to translate these concepts into deliverables. The sheer scale and quality of his output is testament to his organisational and managerial abilities. He thrives under pressure and has displayed the ability to prioritise multiple inputs. In sum, he has consistently demonstrated the capacity to handle increased responsibility. As the first non-FJ QWI White Force Team Leader to oversee CQWI/TLT msns, he has demonstrated immense tactical acumen and an in-depth understanding of broader Defence and Air Power issues. This, combined with his capacity, sharp intellect and eye for detail, identify him as a strong candidate for ACSC. Additionally, he has the potential to undertake a challenging SO1 staff appt in the joint/coalition/HQ arena. Gp Capt Bentley 2009-2010

description: Stockbridge's multiple significant achievements over this reporting period provide clear evidence of his exceptional calibre. He should be justifiably proud that he has delivered the RAF's first Qualified Wpns Instructor(ISR) cse, having conceived the idea only last year. This has involved writing the cse, trg the instructors and then running a highly successful and ground-breaking cse; clearly illustrating his vision, leadership, dedication and drive. This has been particularly impressive when set against the already high workload of his desk. His support to Ops has been outstanding, having contributed significantly to Op success by devising tactics for the employment of ISR in vehicle interdiction, FP and HLS procedures. His ability to effectively apply ISR techniques to support and enhance such a wide spectrum of tactical activities proves not only his immense expertise within the ISR field, but his deep understanding of much broader tactical and operational issues air power issues. His completion of the ISR Planning Guide, the ISR Tactics Book and his ongoing work in the application of ISR in a contested environment and Combat ISR cement his position as the leading ISR expert within the RAF, indeed, his opinion, expertise and influence spreads far; the esteem with which he is held in the joint environment and by our US colleagues are testament to his intellectual and analytical rigour, coupled with his ability communicate well. These attributes combined with his obvious ability to lead, manage a team effectively and his commitment to deliver subordinate trg to the highest standard led to his selection to be a White Force Team Leader. It is the first time a non-FJ QWI has been awarded that status, and on the recent EX CQWI he completed his trg and performed to a characteristically high standard. An impressive year. Wg Cdr S Marshall 2009-2010
